fields.physical_description:
1. box lid; car covered with pale grey/blue paper; on the top is a label printed in colours to show the title; maker's name and an illustration of a model village. On the inside of the lid is another printed sheet showing four illustrations of the model village - different arrangements of the pieces; it also has the maker's name. All four box edges have been damaged and in places are broken; the surface is also dirty and stained. 2. box base; card covered with pale grey/blue paper; it has a raised lining with areas cut away to hold different items and loops of blue elastic to secure other items. In the lower centre area is a second panel; held by thumb tacks; which has the remains of threads also designed to held various items. Underneath are card supports to hold the lining up. *Building structures of wood; painted either white; pale green or red and decorated with paper panels printed in colours to represent windows and doors. These panels are in combinations of red; blue; black; yellow and pale green. Blocks have a base measurement of 1 3/4in square. 
3. church nave; white; with a large arched window and a small arched and shuttered window on each side. 3½in x 1 3/4in sq. 
4. nave roof; pale green; sloping sides and one end and a dormer on each side. L. 3½in 
5. church tower; white; arched door; round window and belfry opening on two opposite sides and two square windows with round centres and belfry opening on the other opposite sides. Ht. 5¼in 
6. tower roof; pale green; four sloping sides forming a point and each side has a dormer window with the front surface painte black. Ht. 3½in 
7. house; white; on each long side are two square windows with round centres; on one end is an arched door and on the other an arched  window. L. 3½in 
8. house roof; red; three sloping sides with a dormer window on one side. L. 3½in 
9. house; white; on each long side are two arched doors and on each end an arched window (these are not in exactly the same position). 
L. 3½in 
10. house roof; grey; four sloping sides with a dormer window on one side. L. 3½in 
11. central block of three part building; white; arched door and round window on opposite side; other sides not decorated. Ht. 3½in 
12. central block roof; tan brown; pyramid shape. Ht. 1in. 
13. central block left side; white; arched and shuttered window on opposite sides and round window on the other two opposite sides. 
Ht. 1 3/4in 
14. left side roof; red; three sloping sides. Ht. 7/8in 
15. central block right side; white; similar to left side but has only one arched and shuttered window. Ht. 1 3/4in 
16. right side roof; red; matching the left side. Ht. 7/8in 
17. stable block; white; it has a partially sloping left side; two long sides covered with `half timbered' effect and square windows panel and a separate small round window. Gt.L. 3½in x gt. ht. 3½in 
18. stable block roof; red; two sloping sides. Ht. 7/8in 
19. `clock tower'; white; green and black arched door on opposite sides and small round green and black windows on the other opposite sides. 1 3/4in cube 
20. clock tower roof; brown; two sloping sides with the ends covered with red and cream paper; at the front end is a chimney block painted white with a red top. gt. ht. 1½in 
*Fencing slats are of different lengths of wood; all stained green. Base measurements are w 7/8in and depth 1/8in. 
21-25. L. 3½in 
26-35. L. 2½in 
36-38. L. 1 3/4in 
*The remaining items; trees; bushes; people and animals; are a combination of card printe in colours mounted on stands of wood. The stands for the trees and flowers are stained green; the ones for the animals and people are plain. Stands for these are narrow with a slit along the centre into which the cardboard slots. 
39. bush; pink and white flowers on green; brown wooden trunk and green wooden base. Ht. 2 3/4in 
40. bush; pink and white flowers on green and blue; brown wooden
trunk; green base missing. Ht. 3½in 
41. tree; pink and white flowers on green; brown wooden trunk and green wooden base. Ht. 4¼in 
42. tree; brown and green foliage; brown wooden trunk and green wooden base. Ht. 5 7/8in 
43. tree; green foliage on light brown branches; brown wooden trunk and green wooden base. Ht. 8in 
44-47. floral hedges; pink and white flowers on green. L. 3½in 
48,49. floral hedges; red and white flowers on green. L. 3½in 
50-56. ornamental fencing decorated with flowers; red and green on a white background. L. 3½in 
57,58. ornamental fencing with a raised end; decorated with flowers; red and green on a white background. L. 3½in 
59. man; blue and white with yellow clogs; holding basket. Ht. 1 3/4in 
60. woman; green; pink and white dress; blue and white striped stockings; checked apron. Ht. 1 3/4in 
61. boy; dark yellow tunic with pale blue; pink and white legs. Ht. 1¼in 62. girl; white dress with pink; yellow apron an blue stockings. Ht. 1½in 63. motor car; open tourer with driver and passenger; dark pink with yellow and white wheels on a background of green and pale pink; driver is in white and passenger in blue. L. 4in 
64. cow; black and white on a background of green; pink and ywllow 
L. 2½in 
65. horse; white with brown tinges on a pink; green and yellow background. L. 2¼in 
66. pig; pink on a green and yellow background. L. 1 3/4in 
*It is not known if there were more people and animals. 
*1868:Brasseur & Chevallier obtained a French patent for a composition bodied doll made of sawdust and glue as an imitation of wood. There may be no connection between the two as the spelling is different; however; this may have been an error at some time in the records.
fields.title: Model Village
fields.marks: E CHEVALIER PARIS; on lower right corner of box label and plain illustrations.
fields.history_note:
References: (Eug) CHEVALIER; Maison fondée en 1865; Aide et Conseils aux Inventeurs. FABRIQUE DE JOUETS; Nouveautés; TECHNO; Constructions - Joyeux Acrobates; Splendides Blocs; Tri-Rameur: Palce des Vosges; 18 (4th) 1924 BOTTIN

Details provided by Monica Burckhardt and taken from the 1924 edition of Bottin. A reference to Chevalier is made under Brasseur & Videlier of Paris; 1865-82; doll makers Brasseur & Chevallier-see note at end.
Bought with B 440-1994 for £300.00; (440-£600); premium £90.00; VAT £15.75 - total amount £1005.75.

Price: £1005.75
